<h3> Why cypress? </h3>
Most Popular Framework, Fast and stable tests, good documentation, easy to learn, strong community

<h3> Code/Text Editors? </h3>
 Visual Studio Code, Atom, Sublime Text, WebStorm (not free)

<h3> How to install and Setup Cypress? </h3>
1. Download npm (firstly npm init and afterwards npm install)
2. npm install cypress
3. Install Prettier? - Automation code formatter (prevent conflicts in code reviews and ..)
npm install prettier
Configure prettier:
-----------------
1. Name the file .prettierrc
2. Add these:
{
    "semi": false,
    "singleQuote": true,
    "useTabs": true, 
    "tabWidth": 2, 
    "bracketSpacing": true,
    "arrowParens": "avoid", 
    "trailingComma": "es5"
}

4. Install another Intelligent Code Completion Dependency

5. Start the cypress: npx cypress open
6. After running the cypress a folder will be created that displayes Cypress
7. right click on the cypress icon and add a file tsconfig.json

=======================================================================================
8. Order to configure the way we are running cypress, we need to configure it in the pachage jason and use the command npm run: cy open in the console 
{
  "name": "cypress",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Automated software testing with cypress",
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "cy:open": "cypress open"
  },
  "keywords": [
    "cypress",
    "testing",
    "automation"
  ],
  "author": "Kristina Ivanova",
  "license": "ISC",
  "dependencies": {
    "cypress": "^9.4.1",
    "prettier": "^2.5.1"
  }
}


